<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<title>Documentation ~ NodCord</title>
		<link rel="shortcut icon" href="<%= logoImage %>" type="image/x-icon" />
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/styles.css" />
		<link
			rel="stylesheet"
			href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bootstrap-icons/1.10.5/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css"
		/>
		<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
	</head>

	<body class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
		<%- include('./partials/header'); %>
		<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row">
			<!-- Sidebar for mobile and larger screens -->
			<aside
				class="lg:w-64 dark:bg-gray-900 text-white h-full lg:h-screen sticky top-0 p-5 shadow-lg lg:block lg:static fixed inset-0 lg:relative lg:flex lg:flex-col z-10 transform -translate-x-full lg:translate-x-0 transition-transform duration-300"
				id="sidebar"
			>
				<button class="lg:hidden text-2xl mb-4" id="closeSidebar">
					&times;
				</button>
				<div class="space-y-2 lg:space-y-4">
					<a
						href="#overview"
						class="block py-3 px-4 text-lg hover:bg-gray-700 rounded transition-colors"
						>Overview</a
					>
					<a
						href="#installation"
						class="block py-3 px-4 text-lg hover:bg-gray-700 rounded transition-colors"
						>Installation</a
					>
					<a
						href="#configuration"
						class="block py-3 px-4 text-lg hover:bg-gray-700 rounded transition-colors"
						>Configuration</a
					>
					<a
						href="#usage"
						class="block py-3 px-4 text-lg hover:bg-gray-700 rounded transition-colors"
						>Usage</a
					>
					<a
						href="#api"
						class="block py-3 px-4 text-lg hover:bg-gray-700 rounded transition-colors"
						>API Reference</a
					>
					<a
						href="#faq"
						class="block py-3 px-4 text-lg hover:bg-gray-700 rounded transition-colors"
						>FAQ</a
					>
					<a
						href="#contact"
						class="block py-3 px-4 text-lg hover:bg-gray-700 rounded transition-colors"
						>Contact</a
					>
				</div>
			</aside>

			<!-- Main content area -->
			<main
				class="flex-1 p-6 m-5 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 shadow-lg rounded-lg"
			>
				<button class="lg:hidden text-2xl mb-4" id="openSidebar">
					&#9776;
					<!-- Burger Menu Icon -->
				</button>

				<!-- Overview Section -->
				<section id="overview">
					<h1
						class="text-3xl font-bold border-b-2 border-gray-700 dark:border-gray-600 pb-2 mb-4"
					>
						Overview
					</h1>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
						Welcome to the NodCord documentation. NodCord is a versatile and
						powerful Discord bot framework that simplifies the process of
						creating and managing your own Discord bots.
					</p>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						With NodCord, you can easily set up, configure, and deploy bots that
						interact with Discord servers, providing a seamless integration
						experience. This documentation will guide you through the
						installation, configuration, and usage of NodCord, along with
						detailed information about its API.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Installation Section -->
				<section id="installation" class="mt-10">
					<h2
						class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-gray-600 dark:border-gray-500 pb-1 mb-4"
					>
						Installation
					</h2>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
						To install NodCord, ensure you have Node.js and npm installed on
						your system. Run the following command to install NodCord:
					</p>
					<pre
						class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto"
					><code>npm install nodcord</code></pre>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mt-4">
						Once installed, you can start building your bot with ease using the
						features provided by NodCord.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Configuration Section -->
				<section id="configuration" class="mt-10">
					<h2
						class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-gray-600 dark:border-gray-500 pb-1 mb-4"
					>
						Configuration
					</h2>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
						After installation, you need to configure NodCord to work with your
						Discord bot. Create a
						<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
							>.env</code
						>
						file in your project directory and add the following environment
						variables:
					</p>
					<pre
						class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto"
					><code>DISCORD_TOKEN=your_discord_token_here
      BOT_PREFIX=!</code></pre>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mt-4">
						These variables will be used by NodCord to authenticate your bot
						with Discord and to set the command prefix for the bot's
						interactions.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Usage Section -->
				<section id="usage" class="mt-10">
					<h2
						class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-gray-600 dark:border-gray-500 pb-1 mb-4"
					>
						Usage
					</h2>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
						To start using NodCord, create an
						<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
							>index.js</code
						>
						file and add the following code to initialize your bot:
					</p>
					<pre
						class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto"
					><code>const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('nodcord');
      const client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages] });

      client.on('ready', () => {
        console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);
      });

      client.login(process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN);</code></pre>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mt-4">
						This script sets up a basic bot that logs in to Discord using the
						token you provided and outputs a message when it is successfully
						connected.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- API Reference Section -->
				<section id="api" class="mt-10">
					<h2
						class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-gray-600 dark:border-gray-500 pb-1 mb-4"
					>
						API Reference
					</h2>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
						NodCord provides a comprehensive API for interacting with Discord.
						Here are some of the main methods:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-4">
						<li>
							<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
								>client.on(event, listener)</code
							>
							- Listens for a specific event.
						</li>
						<li>
							<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
								>client.login(token)</code
							>
							- Logs in to Discord with the provided token.
						</li>
						<li>
							<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
								>client.user.setActivity(activity)</code
							>
							- Sets the bot's activity status.
						</li>
						<li>
							<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
								>client.guilds.cache</code
							>
							- Accesses the cache of guilds (servers) the bot is part of.
						</li>
						<li>
							<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
								>client.channels.cache</code
							>
							- Accesses the cache of channels within the bot's guilds.
						</li>
						<li>
							<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
								>client.users.cache</code
							>
							- Accesses the cache of users that the bot has interacted with.
						</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						For more detailed information, refer to the full API documentation
						included in the NodCord package or visit the official NodCord GitHub
						repository.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- FAQ Section -->
				<section id="faq" class="mt-10">
					<h2
						class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-gray-600 dark:border-gray-500 pb-1 mb-4"
					>
						FAQ
					</h2>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
						Here are some frequently asked questions about NodCord:
					</p>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">What is NodCord?</h3>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						NodCord is a framework for creating Discord bots with ease. It
						provides a robust API and tools to help developers build and manage
						bots quickly.
					</p>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">How do I install NodCord?</h3>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						To install NodCord, run the command
						<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
							>npm install nodcord</code
						>
						in your Node.js project.
					</p>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">
						Where can I find more information about the API?
					</h3>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						The API reference is included in this documentation and can also be
						found in the NodCord GitHub repository, where you can access the
						full list of available methods and features.
					</p>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6">How do I configure my bot?</h3>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						Configuration is done using a
						<code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
							>.env</code
						>
						file where you define your Discord token and bot prefix. This file
						should be placed in the root directory of your project.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Contact Section -->
				<section id="contact" class="mt-10">
					<h2
						class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-gray-600 dark:border-gray-500 pb-1 mb-4"
					>
						Contact
					</h2>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
						If you have any questions or need further assistance, please contact
						us:
					</p>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						Email:
						<a
							href="mailto:support@nodcord.com"
							class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 dark:hover:text-blue-400"
							>support@nodcord.com</a
						>
					</p>
					<p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
						GitHub:
						<a
							href="https://github.com/nodcord"
							class="text-blue-500 hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300 dark:hover:text-blue-400"
							target="_blank"
							>NodCord GitHub</a
						>
					</p>
				</section>
			</main>
		</div>

		<script>
			// JavaScript for handling the sidebar toggle
			document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
				const sidebarToggle = document.getElementById('openSidebar');
				const closeSidebar = document.getElementById('closeSidebar');
				const sidebar = document.getElementById('sidebar');

				if (sidebarToggle) {
					sidebarToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
						sidebar.classList.remove('-translate-x-full');
						sidebar.classList.add('translate-x-0');
					});
				}

				if (closeSidebar) {
					closeSidebar.addEventListener('click', () => {
						sidebar.classList.remove('translate-x-0');
						sidebar.classList.add('-translate-x-full');
					});
				}
			});
		</script>

		<%- include('./partials/footer'); %>
	</body>
</html>
